The paper discusses the development of Content Based Image Retrieval (CBIR) techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the need for an image understanding agent, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the growth of research in semantic image understanding, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
